lead_paragraph: Usman Khawaja hit his country's first century of the series and Peter Handscomb a half century on debut as Australia reached 307 for six with a lead of 48 at end of the second day of the day-night third test against South Africa on Friday.

headline.print_headline: Khawaja Hits Tonne as Australia Take the Lead in Adelaide
